If you modify conf/config.inc or conf/database.conf, remember to give the
apache read-only permissions again (these are overwritten on save):

  bash$> setfacl -m u:apache:r config.inc

These two files might contain passwords, make sure these files are *not* 
readable by world:

  bash$> ls -l config.inc database.conf
  -rw-r-----+ 1 andlov andlov 8110 Sep 14 10:18 config.inc
  -rw-r-----+ 1 andlov andlov 1403 Aug 19 13:01 database.conf

// Anders Lövgren, 2009-09-14
